ws musical responses to globalization in diverse areas that include the major metropolises of India and China and remote settlements in South America and the Arctic. By tracing this long history of world music, Liebersohn shows how global movement has forever changed how we hear music—and indeed, how we feel about the world around us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEthnomusicologyxHistory. 0aEthnomusicology-History. 0aGlobalizationxHistory. 0aGlobalization-History. 0aMusic and globalizationxHistory. 0aMusic and globalization-History. 0aSound recording industryxHistory. 0aSound recording industry-History. 0aWorld musicxHistory and criticism. 0aWorld music-History and criticism. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aArts and Crafts movement.  aacoustics.  acultural brokers.  aethnomusicology.  aglobalization.  aintellectual history.  amusicology.  aphonograph industry.  atransnationalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107119430 cprintz978022662126540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226649306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226649306/original  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  Uni